          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The beauty of SwiftCrossUI is that you can write your app once and have it look native everywhere. For this reason I recommend using DefaultBackend unless you’ve got particular constraints. It uses ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/AppKitBackend",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " on macOS, ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/WinUIBackend",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " on Window, ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/GtkBackend",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " on Linux, and on ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/UIKitBackend",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " on iOS\/tvOS.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "If you’re using DefaultBackend, you can override the underlying backend during compilation by setting the ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "code" : "SCUI_DEFAULT_BACKEND",
                  "type" : "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " environment variable to the name of the desired backend. This is useful when you e.g. want to test the Gtk version of your app while using a Mac. Note that this only works for built-in backends and still requires the chosen backend to be compatible with your machine.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Tip",
          "style" : "tip",
